{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place bread in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place walnuts and cashews in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3-5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr> until roughly chopped. Transfer to bowl with breadcrumbs and set aside.","Place vegetable stock, lentils and water in mixing bowl then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, boil <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>. With simmering basket in place of measuring cup, simmer <nobr>15-20 min\/98°C\/\/speed <\/nobr> until tender. Drain lentils in a fine mesh sieve and set aside. Rinse mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 190°C and line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place garlic, onions and mushrooms in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sunflower seeds, Worcestershire sauce, linseed mixture, reserved breadcrumbs and nuts, reserved lentils, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme then mix <nobr>20 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Place a pastry cutter (Ø 9 cm) on prepared tray and fill with approx. ¼ of mixture, smoothing the surface with the back of a spoon. Remove pastry cutter and repeat with remaining mixture to make 4 equal-sized patties. Bake for 30-40 minutes (190°C) until crispy and brown. Leave to rest on tray for 5 minutes before serving with a salad."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["25 g wholemeal bread, torn in pieces","50 g walnut halves","30 g cashew nuts","1 vegetable stock cube (for 0.5 l), crumbled","100 g red lentils, rinsed","500 g water","1 garlic clove","100 g onions, quartered","150 g chestnut mushrooms, halved","50 g sunflower seeds","15 g Worcestershire sauce","1 Tbsp linseeds, ground, mixed with 3 Tbsp water","½ tsp dried parsley","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","¼ tsp dried thyme","mixed salad leaves, for serving"]}],"id":"r423886","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-YBOvxogtCj8\/XZVPqnaLVqI\/AAAAAAAAc7U\/Zz